00079 template<typename T> inline double calc_sd(vector<T> vec) {
00080   double mean  = accumulate(vec.begin(), vec.end(), 0.0) / vec.size();
00081   double sqsum = inner_product(vec.begin(), vec.end(), vec.begin(), 0.0);
00082   double stdev = sqrt(sqsum / vec.size() - mean * mean);
00083   return stdev;
00084 }

00087 // define a sorter to sort by the Mate Position
00088 typedef std::binary_function<Read, Read, bool> AlignmentSortBase;
00089 struct ByMatePosition : public AlignmentSortBase {
00090   
00091   // ctor
00092   ByMatePosition(const BamTools::Algorithms::Sort::Order& order = BamTools::Algorithms::Sort::AscendingOrder)
00093     : m_order(order) { }
00094   
00095   // comparison function
00096   bool operator()(const Read& lhs, const Read& rhs) {
00097     
00098     // force unmapped aligmnents to end
00099     if ( r_mid(lhs) == -1 ) return false;
00100     if ( r_mid(rhs) == -1 ) return true;
00101     
00102     // if on same reference, sort on position
00103     if ( r_mid(lhs) == r_mid(rhs) )
00104       return BamTools::Algorithms::Sort::sort_helper(m_order, r_mpos(lhs), r_mpos(rhs));
00105     
00106     // otherwise sort on reference ID
00107     return BamTools::Algorithms::Sort::sort_helper(m_order, r_mid(lhs), r_mid(rhs));
00108   }
00109   // used by BamMultiReader internals
00110   static inline bool UsesCharData(void) { return false; }
00111   
00112   // data members
00113   private:
00114   const BamTools::Algorithms::Sort::Order m_order;
00115 };

00147 // define a sorter to sort by the Mate Position
00148 typedef std::binary_function<Read, Read, bool> AlignmentSortBase;
00149 struct ByReadAndMatePosition : public AlignmentSortBase {
00150   
00151   // ctor
00152   ByReadAndMatePosition(const BamTools::Algorithms::Sort::Order& order = BamTools::Algorithms::Sort::AscendingOrder)
00153     : m_order(order) { }
00154 
00155   // comparison function
00156   bool operator()(const Read& lhs, const Read& rhs) {
00157 
00158     // set the lower nums
00159     int Lref, Lpos, Rref, Rpos;
00160 
00161     // read is lower
00162     if ( (r_id(lhs) < r_mid(lhs)) || (r_id(lhs) == r_mid(lhs) && r_pos(lhs) < r_mpos(lhs))) {
00163       Lref = r_id(lhs);
00164       Lpos = r_pos(lhs);
00165     // mate is lower
00166     } else {
00167       Lref = r_mid(lhs);
00168       Lpos = r_mpos(lhs);
00169     }
00170     
00171     // read is lower
00172     if ( (r_id(rhs) < r_mid(rhs)) || (r_id(rhs) == r_mid(rhs) && r_pos(rhs) < r_mpos(rhs))) {
00173       Rref = r_id(rhs);
00174       Rpos = r_pos(rhs);
00175     // mate is lower
00176     } else {
00177       Rref = r_mid(rhs);
00178       Rpos = r_mpos(rhs);
00179     }
00180 
00181     // force unmapped aligmnents to end
00182     if ( Lref == -1) return false;
00183     if ( Rref == -1) return true;
00184     
00185     // if on same reference, sort on position
00186     if ( Lref == Rref )
00187       return BamTools::Algorithms::Sort::sort_helper(m_order, Lpos, Rpos);
00188     
00189     // otherwise sort on reference ID
00190     return BamTools::Algorithms::Sort::sort_helper(m_order, Lref, Rref);
00191   }
00192   // used by BamMultiReader internals
00193   static inline bool UsesCharData(void) { return false; }
00194   
00195   // data members
00196   private:
00197   const BamTools::Algorithms::Sort::Order m_order;
00198 };

00216   void stop(string part) { 
00217     times[part] += (clock() - curr_clock); 
00218     curr_clock = clock();
00219   }
00220   void start() { curr_clock = clock(); }

00223   friend ostream& operator<<(ostream &out, const SnowTimer st) {
00224 
00225     double total_time = 0;
00226     for (auto& i : st.times)
00227       total_time += i.second;
00228     if (total_time == 0)
00229       return out;

00232     
00233     auto itr = st.times.find("r");
00234     auto itm = st.times.find("m");

00236     auto ita = st.times.find("as");
00237     auto itb = st.times.find("bw");
00238     auto its = st.times.find("sw");
00239 
00240     sprintf (buffer, "R: %2d%% M: %2d%% D: %2d%% A: %2d%% B: %2d%% S: %2d%%", 
00241              SnowTools::percentCalc<double>(itr->second, total_time),
00242              SnowTools::percentCalc<double>(itm->second, total_time),

00244              SnowTools::percentCalc<double>(ita->second, total_time),
